psagot investment house  wikipedia psagot investment house from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search psagot investment house ltd psagot tower in tel aviv on the right type private industry financial services predecessor ofek securities and investments founded  psagot mutual funds founded  founded   headquarters tel aviv israel products pension funds life insurance provident funds severance pay funds mutual funds exchangetraded notes services brokerage and research services aum ₪  billion owner apax partners number of employees  website wwwpsagotcoilenghomepageaspx the psagot investment house hebrew פסגות בית השקעות‎‎ is an israeli investment firm and the countrys largest pension fund manager controlled by apax partners since  the firm manages assets and capital totalling  billion psagot is located on ahad haam street in tel aviv in close proximity to the tel aviv stock exchange contents  background  isa investigations  see also  references  external links backgroundedit the psagot investment house was established in  through the merger of psagot mutual funds and psagot ofek a portfolio management company founded by gabriella ravid in  in  subsequent to the bachar reform bank leumi finalized the sale of psagot to york capital management a new yorkbased investment firm york capital sold its stake in the company  to apax partners in  at  million the apax takeover of psagot was israels largest private equity deal in  under the direction of roy vermus as ceo beginning in  psagot grew to become israels largest investment firm through a series of strategic fund acquisitions it acquired a provident fund managing nis billion in assets from prisma investment house ltd in  and made its first major pension fund acquisition in  after outbidding a competitor for control of the histadrut leumit fund which managed nis billion in assets in addition vermus shut down psagots underwriting unit forbes israel ranked vermus the fourth most influential young israeli in  isa investigationsedit in  when psagot was still owned by bank leumi the israel securities authority launched an investigation into the firms dealings for suspected violations of the regulation of investment advice and investment portfolio management law  the investigation went on for a year and culminated in a raid of psagots offices and the taking in of the firms executives for questioning in late  the impetus for the investigation was a psagot fund having raised nis billion in a single day psagot founder and general manager gabriella ravid resigned along with her deputy in late  in  bank leumi agreed to pay a fine of nis million as part of a plea bargain agreement in  police arrested three senior psagot employees on charges that they were involved in manipulating the prices of government and corporate bonds in order to redound greater profits to the firm and inflate their bonuses in the years – an investigation conducted by the isa concluded with psagot agreeing to pay a fine of nis million as part of a plea bargain psagot ceo at the time roy vermus was subsequently compelled to resign from the firm after the supreme court rejected an appeal he filed against his forced ouster from the company see alsoedit economy of israel venture capital in israel referencesedit  gewirtz jason  february  israels business elite weigh irans nuclear threat cnbc retrieved  february    contact us psagot investment house retrieved  february    psagot group – israel’s largest investment house duns  retrieved  february    a b bergman roee  december  ravid silbiger quit psagot ofek globes retrieved  march    dagan ram  november  york capital buys leumis psagot ofek haaretz retrieved  february    rochvarger michael  october  apax takeover of psagot falls apart haaretz retrieved  february    psagot buyout boosts private equity total to twoyear high globes  february  retrieved  march    a b peer eran  december  roy vermus leaves psagot globes retrieved  march    hazani golan raz hadar  se